<section xml:id="section-assignment-week7">
  <title>Week 7 Assignment</title>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Invert these matrices. (Show the steps of your process, though
        you don't need to show every row operation in the row
        reduction.) (6)
        <ol>
          <li><me>
            \begin{pmatrix}
              1 \amp -1 \amp -1 \\
              0 \amp 2 \amp 1 \\
              2 \amp -2 \amp 3
            \end{pmatrix}
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \begin{pmatrix}
              -3 \amp 0 \amp -1 \\
              0 \amp -1 \amp 0 \\
              4 \amp 2 \amp 2
            \end{pmatrix}
          </me></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider the transformation defined by this matrix. (6)
        <me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            -1 \amp 0 \amp -1 \\
            0 \amp 1 \amp 2 \\
            3 \amp -1 \amp -1
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><p>
          What does this matrix do to the line
          <me>
            \Span \left\{ \begin{pmatrix}
              1 \\ 1 \\ 3\
            \end{pmatrix} \right\} 
          </me>.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          What does this matrix do to the plane given by the equation     
          <me>
            x - y - z = 0 
          </me>.
        </p></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider this matrix and its associated transformation. (8) 
        <me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            -3 \amp -1 \amp 0 \\
            -1 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\
            1 \amp 1 \amp 1
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the kernel and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the image and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Check that the dimension of the image and the kernel add up
          to the dimension of the domain.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find the rank of the matrix. 
        </p></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider this matrix and its associated transformation. (8) 
        <me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
            0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
            0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the kernel and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the image and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Check that the dimension of the image and the kernel add up
          to the dimension of the domain.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find the rank of the matrix. 
        </p></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        How many <m>4 \times 4</m> matrices have a one-dimensional
        rowspace. What do these matrices look like. Can you think of a
        way of classifying or indexing them. What is the dimension of
        this space of matrices? (6) 
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>
